Life has a way of surprising us, doesn't it? No matter how precisely we plan or how diligently we work towards whatever our goals, there are moments when things take an unexpected turn. Those just beyond our little grasp. There's (not really) simple truth: sometimes, something is out of control. However, remember that it's not the lack of control that defines us --rather, it's our response to those situations that matter more.

---

For me personally, acceptance **isn't** about resignation, nor a failure. it's about acknowledging the reality of the moment **without** allowing it to control our emotional state moreover our life. In the face of uncertainty, acceptance can be your powerful anchor. I personally still learn this, i forgot when/where was the first time someone talk about this kind of mindset, but i believe this will survive us from the burden of unnecessary worry and stress.

